Reasoning: The paper discusses the networked infrastructure of knowledge-based innovation systems, which involves the interaction of various institutions and the measurement of their relations. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of scientometric and webometric data implies a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the dynamics of the Triple Helix model, which involves the interaction of university, industry, and government institutions, suggesting that it may belong to the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Systems and Control (cs.SD).
